The dataset was randomly divided into 70% for training and 30% for testing. Model performance was evaluated using the coefficient of determination (R



      2


), mean absolute error (MAE), and root mean square error (RMSE), calculated exclusively on the unseen test set. No hyperparameter tuning or model adjustment was conducted using the test data to avoid optimistic bias and to support an unbiased assessment of generalization performance.
